studyDesigns.name: Study Design
studyDesigns.rationale: Protocol-defined study design for investigating efficacy and safety

arms.name: Canagliflozin 100 mg
arms.description: Participants receive canagliflozin 100 mg orally once daily (QD) before the first meal of the day.

arms.name: Placebo
arms.description: Participants receive matching placebo capsules orally once daily (QD) before the first meal of the day.

studyCohorts.name: CKD Stage 3
studyCohorts.characteristic: eGFR >=30 to <60 mL/min/1.73m2 (Targeting approximately 60% of total population)

studyCohorts.name: CKD Stage 2
studyCohorts.characteristic: eGFR >=60 to <90 mL/min/1.73m2 (Targeting approximately 40% of total population)

population.name: Study Population
population.description: Target population defined by eligibility criteria

objectives.name: Primary Efficacy Objective
objectives.text: In subjects with T2DM, Stage 2 or 3 CKD and macroalbuminuria who are receiving standard of care, to assess the efficacy of canagliflozin relative to placebo in reducing: The composite endpoint of end-stage kidney disease (ESKD), doubling of serum creatinine, and renal or cardiovascular (CV) death

objectives.name: Secondary Efficacy Objective 1
objectives.text: To assess the efficacy of canagliflozin relative to placebo in reducing: The composite endpoint of CV death and hospitalized congestive heart failure

objectives.name: Secondary Efficacy Objective 2
objectives.text: To assess the efficacy of canagliflozin relative to placebo in reducing: The composite endpoint of CV death, non-fatal myocardial infarction (MI), and non-fatal stroke (ie, 3-point major adverse cardiac event [MACE])

objectives.name: Secondary Efficacy Objective 3
objectives.text: To assess the efficacy of canagliflozin relative to placebo in reducing: Hospitalized congestive heart failure

objectives.name: Secondary Efficacy Objective 4
objectives.text: To assess the efficacy of canagliflozin relative to placebo in reducing: The renal composite endpoint of ESKD, doubling of serum creatinine, and renal death

objectives.name: Secondary Efficacy Objective 5
objectives.text: To assess the efficacy of canagliflozin relative to placebo in reducing: CV death

objectives.name: Secondary Efficacy Objective 6
objectives.text: To assess the efficacy of canagliflozin relative to placebo in reducing: All-cause death

objectives.name: Secondary Efficacy Objective 7
objectives.text: To assess the efficacy of canagliflozin relative to placebo in reducing: The CV composite endpoint of CV death, non-fatal MI, non-fatal stroke, hospitalized congestive heart failure, and hospitalized unstable angina

objectives.name: Exploratory Objective 1
objectives.text: To assess the efficacy of canagliflozin relative to placebo in reducing: The composite endpoint of ESKD and renal or CV death

objectives.name: Exploratory Objective 2
objectives.text: To assess the impact of canagliflozin relative to placebo on: Changes in estimated glomerular filtration rate (eGFR) over time

objectives.name: Exploratory Objective 3
objectives.text: To assess the impact of canagliflozin relative to placebo on: Changes in albuminuria over time

objectives.name: Safety Objective
objectives.text: To assess the overall safety and tolerability of canagliflozin.

endpoints.name: Primary Efficacy Outcome
endpoints.text: The first occurrence of ESKD, doubling of serum creatinine, and renal or CV death.

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Outcome 1
endpoints.text: The composite endpoint of CV death and hospitalized congestive heart failure

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Outcome 2
endpoints.text: The composite endpoint of CV death, non-fatal MI, and non-fatal stroke (ie, 3-point MACE)

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Outcome 4
endpoints.text: The renal composite endpoint of ESKD, doubling of serum creatinine and renal death

endpoints.name: Secondary Efficacy Outcome 7
endpoints.text: The CV composite endpoint of CV death, non-fatal MI, non-fatal stroke, hospitalized congestive heart failure, and hospitalized unstable angina

endpoints.name: Exploratory Efficacy Outcome 1
endpoints.text: Reduction in the composite endpoint of ESKD and renal or CV death

endpoints.name: Safety Outcomes
endpoints.text: The overall safety and tolerability of canagliflozin. The safety evaluations include the collection of adverse events, laboratory tests, vital signs (pulse, blood pressure), physical examination, and body weight.

estimands.name: Primary Efficacy Estimand
estimands.populationSummary: Adults (≥30 years) with T2DM, Stage 2 or 3 CKD (eGFR 30 to <90 mL/min/1.73m2), and macroalbuminuria (UACR >300 to ≤5000 mg/g) on stable ACEi or ARB therapy. Summary measure: Hazard ratio.

intercurrentEvents.name: Treatment discontinuation
intercurrentEvents.text: Premature discontinuation of study drug for any reason

intercurrentEvents.name: Death
intercurrentEvents.text: Death due to non-renal and non-CV causes

intercurrentEvents.name: Initiation of rescue medication
intercurrentEvents.text: Use of additional antihyperglycemic or antihypertensive therapies to reach clinical goals

exits.name: Early Treatment Discontinuation
exits.description: Subjects who discontinue study drug prematurely must still attend all subsequent study visits until GTED.

exits.name: Study Completion
exits.description: The study ends at the Global Trial End Date (GTED), estimated at 5 to 5.5 years.

notes.text: a. EOS = end-of-study; EOT = end-of-treatment; EW=early withdrawal; HbA1c =hemoglobin A1c; CBC = complete blood count; SMBG = self-monitored blood glucose; TC = telephone contact.
b. Subjects who fail protocol-specified screening criteria for study entry may be rescreened at the discretion of the investigator.
c. At Week 39 and at the midpoint between office visits after Week 52, telephone contact will be made to check the subject's status.
d. This visit will occur at Week 52, 104, 156, 208, and 260.
e. This telephone contact will occur at Week 39, 65, 91, 117, 143, 169, 195, 221, 247, and 273.
f. This visit will occur at Week 26, 78, 130, 182, 234 and 286.
g. End-of-treatment/end-of-study/early withdrawal evaluations will be performed when the double-blind treatment phase of the study is ended.
h. A telephone follow-up contact (or optional study visit) will be conducted for all subjects approximately 30 days (+/- 12 days) after the last dose.
e. This telephone contact will occur at Week 39, 65, 91, 117, 143, 169, 195, 221, 247, and 273.

titles.text: A Randomized, Double-blind, Event-driven, Placebo-controlled, Multicenter Study of the Effects of Canagliflozin on Renal and Cardiovascular Outcomes in Subjects With Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus and Diabetic Nephropathy
Canagliflozin and Renal Events in Diabetes with Established Nephropathy Clinical Evaluation Trial

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: HbA1c level
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: HbA1c level ≤12.0% for the study entry.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: eGFR range
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Chronic kidney disease (CKD) Stage 3 (eGFR ≥30 to <60 mL/min/1.73m2) or CKD Stage 2 (eGFR ≥60 to <90 mL/min/1.73m2).

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: ACEi or ARB therapy
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: All subjects must be on a stable, maximum tolerated labeled daily dose of ACEi or ARB for at least 4 weeks prior to randomization.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Tubal occlusion clarification
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Clarification to definition of tubal occlusion for female participants.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Blood pressure reassessment
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Clarification regarding reassessment of blood pressure.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Hyperkalemia history
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Removed previous history of hyperkalemia from exclusion criteria.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Cardiovascular events
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Myocardial infarction, unstable angina, revascularization procedure (eg, stent or bypass graft surgery), or cerebrovascular accident prior to randomization.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Major surgery
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Major surgery (ie, requiring general anesthesia) within 12 weeks before screening, or has not fully recovered from surgery. Note: Subjects with planned surgical procedures to be conducted under local anesthesia may participate.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Amputation risk
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: History of atraumatic amputation within past 12 months of screening, or an active skin ulcer, osteomyelitis, gangrene, or critical ischemia of the lower extremity within 6 months of screening.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: MRA or DRI therapy
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Current use of mineralocorticoid antagonist (MRA) or direct renin inhibitor (DRI). Note: Subjects who are off therapy with MRA or DRI for at least 8 weeks prior to randomization may be considered eligible.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: SGLT2 inhibitor use
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Current use of an SGLT2 inhibitor prior to randomization.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Prior canagliflozin exposure
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Current participation in another canagliflozin study or previously exposed to canagliflozin in a prior canagliflozin study.

studyInterventions.name: Canagliflozin
studyInterventions.description: Sodium-glucose co-transporter 2 (SGLT2) inhibitor for the treatment of type 2 diabetes mellitus and diabetic nephropathy.

studyInterventions.name: Placebo
studyInterventions.description: Matching placebo capsules for single-blind run-in and double-blind treatment phases.

studyInterventions.name: ACEi or ARB
studyInterventions.description: Maximum tolerated labeled daily dose of an angiotensin-converting enzyme inhibitor or angiotensin receptor blocker required for at least 4 weeks prior to randomization.

studyInterventions.name: Antihyperglycemic agents (AHA)
studyInterventions.description: Background AHA regimen adjusted to achieve glycemic goals using standard local guidelines.

studyInterventions.name: Mineralocorticoid receptor antagonist (MRA)
studyInterventions.description: Restricted post-baseline use permitted if medically necessary; requires frequent monitoring of serum potassium.

studyInterventions.name: Direct renin inhibitor (DRI)
studyInterventions.description: Subjects must be off therapy for at least 8 weeks prior to randomization.

studyInterventions.name: SGLT2 inhibitors
studyInterventions.description: Current use of other SGLT2 inhibitors is prohibited.

amendments.name: Amendment INT-6
amendments.summary: The primary reason for the amendment is to decrease the number of primary composite events required for the interim analysis from 540 to 405. In addition, 2 new secondary endpoints have been added and secondary endpoints have been reordered.

amendments.name: Amendment INT-5
amendments.summary: The primary reason to amend the study protocol is to include new safety information and guidance regarding subject management surrounding the event of lower extremity amputations.

amendments.name: Amendment INT-4
amendments.summary: To provide further clarifications regarding ACEi or ARB therapy and modify text for clarity across multiple sections including study design and exclusion criteria.

amendments.name: Amendment INT-3
amendments.summary: The summary for this amendment was not explicitly detailed in the provided text, but involved modifications to study design and exclusion criteria.

amendments.name: Amendment INT-2
amendments.summary: To revise inclusion criteria to allow patients with higher baseline HbA1c values who may benefit from the study treatment to participate in the study. In addition, changes to the prescreening assessment are intended to allow a wider range of measures to prescreen subjects for albuminuria/proteinuria.

amendments.name: Amendment INT-1
amendments.summary: The primary reason for the amendment to the protocol is to reflect recommendations from the United States (US) Food and Drug Administration (FDA) for study 28431754DNE3001.

conditions.name: Run-in Compliance
conditions.text: Subjects must achieve >=80% compliance by pill count during the 2-week single-blind placebo run-in period.

conditions.name: ESKD Definition
conditions.description: Criteria for End-Stage Kidney Disease endpoint
conditions.text: Initiation of maintenance dialysis for at least 1 month, renal transplantation, or sustained eGFR <15 mL/min/1.73m2 confirmed by repeat measure >=30 days later.

study.name: A Randomized, Double-blind, Event-driven, Placebo-controlled, Multicenter Study of the Effects of Canagliflozin on Renal and Cardiovascular Outcomes in Subjects With Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus and Diabetic Nephropathy

transitionRules.name: Screening to Run-in
transitionRules.text: Qualified subjects enter single-blind placebo run-in at Week -2.

transitionRules.name: Randomization Transition
transitionRules.text: Subjects compliant during run-in are randomly assigned 1:1 to canagliflozin or placebo.

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation for Renal Events
transitionRules.text: Study medication is discontinued when chronic dialysis or renal transplant is initiated.

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation for DKA
transitionRules.text: Double-blind study drug should be permanently discontinued for any subject who experiences a serious adverse event of biochemically-confirmed DKA.

commentAnnotations.text: Janssen Research & Development is a global organization that operates through different legal entities in various countries.
Double-blind study drug should be permanently discontinued for any subject who experiences a serious adverse event of biochemically-confirmed DKA.
For fasting plasma glucose and lipids, subjects must be fasting for at least 8 hours before blood sample collection.
While positive reagent strip analysis (eg, dipstick ≥2+) may be suggestive of albuminuria/proteinuria, any positive reagent strip findings must be accompanied by one of the specified measures.

studyDefinitionDocumentVersions.description: Decrease primary composite events for interim analysis from 540 to 405; added 2 new secondary endpoints.
Include new safety information and guidance regarding lower extremity amputations.
Sample size expansion and removal of eGFR 60 to <90 cap.

studyAmendmentImpacts.description: Reduction in the number of primary composite events required for the interim analysis from 540 to 405.
Addition of 3-point MACE and hospitalized congestive heart failure as new secondary endpoints.
Designation of pancreatitis as an adverse event of special interest requiring 24-hour reporting.
New exclusion criteria for subjects at high risk of lower extremity amputation.

studyAmendmentReasons.reasonText: Decrease the number of primary composite events required for the interim analysis to allow for earlier detection of beneficial effects.
Include new safety information and guidance regarding subject management surrounding the event of lower extremity amputations.
Slower than expected recruitment early in the study required sample size expansion to maintain study timeline.

studyChanges.summary: Reduced the number of primary composite events required for the interim analysis.
Clarified that study medication is discontinued when chronic dialysis or renal transplant is initiated.

studyChanges.beforeText: The Lan-DeMets alpha spending function approach will be used
studyChanges.afterText: The alpha spending function will be used
studyChanges.summary: Simplified the description of the statistical method used for alpha spending.
Increased the upper limit of HbA1c level for study entry.

studyChanges.afterText: Exclusion criteria 16: history of atraumatic amputation within past 12 months, or active skin ulcer, osteomyelitis, gangrene, or critical ischemia within 6 months.
studyChanges.summary: Added exclusion criteria for subjects at risk of amputation.
